title: Advice from Legends
description:
Pepper is pleased to celebrate Jazz Appreciation Month alongside the Smithsonian Institute, Jazz at Lincoln Center, Jazz Education Network, and the many men and women who love this quintessentially American art form. Over the past few years, we’ve conducted interviews with some of the top names in modern jazz.  So far, we’ve interviewed such heavy hitters as Pat Martino, Roger Ingram, David Liebman, and Paquito D’Rivera. You can see all these interviews and more on the Cued In Jazz page: http://blogs.jwpepper.com/index.php/category/jazz/?utm_source=youtube&utm_medium=youtube&utm_campaign=jazz_100&utm_content=JAM_video

There are more interviews to come. Next up is Eddie Palmieri, followed by Arturo Sandoval and Christian McBride. For now, we've collected some of the best advice these jazz greats have for younger jazz musicians. Please enjoy this video and share with your fellow jazz lovers!

Read the blog: http://blogs.jwpepper.com/index.php/jazz-100-advice-from-legends/?utm_source=youtube&utm_medium=youtube&utm_campaign=jazz_100&utm_content=JAM_video
